// Example: an explicit conflict — two facts violate an axiom.

FACT Animal.B has flying
FACT Animal.B has swimming

AXIOM fly_xor_swim:
    EXCLUSIVE
        Animal.B has flying
        Animal.B has swimming

CHECK Animal.B

// Expected result:
// CONFLICT  fly_xor_swim
//   FACT Animal.B has flying    [line 3]
//   FACT Animal.B has swimming  [line 4]
//   → EXCLUSIVE: at most one may be TRUE
